# AI-Driven Performance Review Platform — Product Requirements

---

## 🚀 Overview

We are building an enterprise-grade, AI-augmented performance management system, inspired by platforms like Lattice and 15Five, to simplify performance management for HR teams, managers, and employees.

This document defines the exact scope for MVP development.

---

## 🎯 Core Modules & Features

### 1️⃣ OKR & Goal Management

* Create, assign, and track Objectives and Key Results.
* Hierarchical structure supported:

  * Company → Department → Team → Individual OKRs.
* Roles allowed to create/assign OKRs: Admin, HR, Manager.
* All users can view OKRs.
* OKRs tagging supported.
* Goal comments and updates allowed.
* Visual progress tracking dashboards.

---

### 2️⃣ Continuous Feedback Module

* Feedback can be given anytime.
* Public and private feedback options.
* Feedback can be provided between any two users (all roles).
* Skill tags are user-created (free tagging).
* Feedback tagging for:

  * Skills
  * Company values
  * Initiatives

---

### 3️⃣ Performance Reviews (360° Reviews)

* Customizable review cycles: Quarterly, Half-Yearly, Annual or fully custom.
* Only 1 active review cycle allowed per employee.
* Adding/removing participants mid-cycle supported:

  * If participant is removed, review data for the period they were in cycle remains.
* Review cycle components:

  * Self-assessment
  * Peer reviews
  * Manager reviews
  * Upward reviews
* Configurable review templates:

  * Competency-based questions
  * Open-ended questions
  * Rating scales
* Anonymity option for peer reviews.
* Review workflows: automatic assignments, reminders, approvals.

---

### 4️⃣ Manager–Report Chain Logic

* Single direct manager per employee supported.
* Automatic chain detection for review assignments.
* Multiple manager support deferred to future versions.

---

### 5️⃣ Reviewer Workload View

* Managers will have a dashboard to view all pending reviews across their direct and indirect reports.

---

## 🤖 AI-Powered Features

### 6️⃣ Auto-Generated Peer Review Suggestions

* "Suggest Draft" button available when starting peer/manager reviews.
* AI uses:

  * Past feedback history
  * OKR/goal progress data
* No external meeting notes or project data in MVP.

### 7️⃣ Self-Assessment Summarizer

* After employee submits self-assessment, they can click "Summarize" to generate:

  * Key themes
  * Strengths & weaknesses
  * Impact statements

### 8️⃣ Sentiment Analysis

* Basic sentiment scoring: positive / neutral / negative.
* AI flags vague or ambiguous responses.

---

## 📊 Analytics & Dashboards

* Role-specific dashboards:

  * HR Dashboard:

    * Org-wide OKR progress
    * Review completion status
    * Company-wide feedback trends
    * Sentiment trends
  * Manager Dashboard:

    * Team OKR progress
    * Team feedback summaries
    * Pending review statuses
* Export reports as CSV/PDF.

